{
  "texts": [
    "Their model relies on extensively augmented training data, and as such acknowledges potential biases in fossil pollen classification accuracy due to variability in pollen formation and sample distribution.",
    "Pant et al. (2020) present a modified ResNeXt model for identifying and classifying algal Pediastrum species from images.",
    "This approach aims to improve the speed and accuracy of algal classification, which is critical for ecological and environmental research.",
    "The model is evaluated on an augmented dataset, on which it performs well: it has yet to be tested in real-world scenarios and thus it is unclear how the model will perform in practice.",
    "Lastly, Adaïmé et al. (2024) introduce a novel approach to the phylogenetic placement of extinct pollen morphotypes by combining CNNs with MLP networks."
  ]
}